Chelsea’s squad to face Sevilla in the UEFA Champions League on Wednesday night has been revealed. According to Football London, Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, has released a full squad of 25 players to tackle Sevilla in Spain. DAILY POST recalls that Chelsea received a huge injury boost after defender, Ben Chilwell, confirmed that he was ready for the Sevilla clash. Chelsea head to the game after playing a 0-0 draw with Tottenham Hotspur in the Premier League last weekend. Chelsea’s full squad against Sevilla: Goalkeepers: Edouard Mendy, Kepa Arrizabalaga and Willy Caballero. Defenders: Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Thiago Silva, Kurt Zouma, Andreas Christensen, Antonio Rudiger, Fikayo Tomori, Ben Chilwell, Marcos Alonso and Emerson Palmieri. Midfielders: N’Golo Kante, Mateo Kovacic, Jorginho, Billy Gilmour, Mason Mount, Kai Havertz, Hakim Ziyech, Callum Hudson-Odoi and Christian Pulisic. Forwards: Timo Werner, Tammy Abraham and Olivier Giroud. The kick-off time for the game is 9 pm.